But mark the Rustic, haggis fed,<br />
The trembling earth resounds his tread.<br />
Clap in his wallie nieve a blade,<br />
He'll mak it whistle;<br />
An' legs an' arms, an' heads will sned,<br />
Like taps o' thristle.<br />
